### User Request Management ###

# Get Pending Requests
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/requests/pending

# Get Specific Request
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/requests/{requestId}

# Approve User Request
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/requests/{requestId}/approve
Content-Type: application/json

"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001"

# Reject User Request
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/requests/{requestId}/reject
Content-Type: application/json

"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001"

### Connect Requests ###

# Send Connect Request (sender ID in route, receiver ID in body)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/sender/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "receiverId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
  "message": "Hi, I'd like to connect with you!"
}

# Accept Connect Request (receiver ID and sender ID in route)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/receiver/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002/accept/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

# Reject Connect Request (receiver ID and sender ID in route)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/receiver/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002/reject/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

# Get Pending Connect Requests (receiver ID in route - shows requests sent TO this user)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/receiver/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002/pending

# Get Sent Connect Requests (sender ID in route - shows requests sent BY this user)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/sender/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/sent

# Check Connection Status (sender and receiver IDs in route)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/connectrequest/connected/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002
